    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 27-SI SERIES, TYPE 200 - REPAIR PROCEDURES - REASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>To install the slip ring end frame assembly to the rotor and drive end frame assembly;</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the tape over the bearing and shaft then make sure the shaft is perfectly clean of
                tape deposits.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert a retaining pin through the holes in the slip ring end frame to hold up the
                brushes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully install the shaft into the slip ring end frame assembly to avoid damage to the
                seal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After tightening the through bolts remove the brush retaining pin to allow the brushes to
                contact the slip rings.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
